# Pi extensions (this playground)

Official reference: [extensions.md](https://github.com/badlogic/pi-mono/blob/main/packages/coding-agent/docs/extensions.md) (Pi runs TypeScript via jiti; `export default function (pi: ExtensionAPI) { … }`).

## When adding or changing extensions

1. **Implement** the real module under `extensions/<name>.ts` (or a subfolder with helpers). Match style of existing files: types from `@mariozechner/pi-coding-agent`, `./themeMap.ts` for `applyExtensionDefaults(import.meta.url, ctx)` in `session_start` where appropriate.
2. **Register** `registerTool`, `registerCommand`, and `registerShortcut` at the **top level** of the extension function (not inside async handlers), or Pi may drop them.
3. **Auto-load (project)**  
   - Add a **shim** only: `.pi/extensions/<name>.ts` containing  
     `export { default } from "../../extensions/<name>.ts";`  
   - **Never** put `themeMap.ts` or other helpers under `.pi/extensions/` — Pi loads **every** `*.ts` there as an extension and will error if there is no valid default factory.
4. **Register in** `.pi/settings.json` under `"extensions": [ ".pi/extensions/…" ]` (paths relative to repo root). Run **`/reload`** in Pi after edits.
5. **Quick test** without editing settings: `pi -e extensions/<name>.ts` (optionally stack `-e`).

## Integrating others’ work

- **npm / git Pi packages**: declare in `agent/settings.json` (`npm:…`, `git:…`); entrypoints come from each package’s `package.json` → `pi.extensions`. See `extensions/extension-picker.ts` for discovery patterns.
- **Single file from disk**: add an absolute path to `extensions` in settings (per upstream docs), or vendor into `extensions/` and use the shim pattern.

